 * Copyright 2020 Your Company Name
 */
```

You can use a search and replace function in your text editor. In Notepad++, for instance, you would go to `Search > Replace`, then in the "Find what" field, you would enter the copyright notice, and leave the "Replace with" field empty. Click "Replace All" to remove it.

Alternatively, you can write a simple PHP script to automate this process:

```php
<?php
$directory = '/path/to/your/php/code/directory';
$pattern = '/\/\*\*\s*Copyright.*\n\s*\*\//m';

if (is_dir($directory)) {
    $files = scandir($directory);
    foreach ($files as $file) {
        if (is_file($file) && pathinfo($file, PATHINFO_EXTENSION) === 'php') {
            $content = file_get_contents($file);
            if (preg_match($pattern, $content)) {
                $newContent = preg_replace($pattern, '', $content);
                file_put_contents($file, $newContent);
            }
        }
    }
} else {
    echo "$directory is not a directory.";
}
?>
```

This script will search through all PHP files in a specified directory and remove any copyright notices that match the pattern. Keep in mind that this is a basic example and might need to be adjusted based on the specifics of your copyright notices and file structure.

